The paper discusses component-based software engineering and model-driven engineering, which are both subfields of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper proposes a mechanism for transforming platform-independent logical component and connector architectures into platform-specific implementations, which involves the use of code libraries (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the benefits of postponing commitment to a specific platform, which is a key aspect of software development (cs.SD). The paper involves the design and implementation of software systems, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of models and libraries, which are also relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
